1. *Major* je danas bio na vežbi sa vojnicima. (The *major* was on a drill with soldiers today.)
2. Naša kompanija je danas dobila novog *majora*. (Our company got a new *major* today.)
3. *Majorov* govor je bio inspirativan za sve nas. (The *major's* speech was inspiring for all of us.)
4. Vojska je organizovala svečanu paradu u čast odlaska u penziju jednog *majora*. (The army organized a solemn parade in honor of the retirement of a *major*.)
5. *Majorstvo* je visoko vojničko zvanje. (*Majorship* is a high military rank.)
6. *Majora* je odlikovala hrabrost u borbi. (*Major* was decorated for bravery in combat.)
7. Naš *major* je bio zadužen za logistiku. (Our *major* was responsible for logistics.)
8. *Majoru* je povereno rukovođenje vojnom operacijom. (*Major* was entrusted with the leadership of a military operation.)
9. Ovaj *major* je veteran mnogih vojnih sukoba. (This *major* is a veteran of many military conflicts.)
10. *Majorima* je neophodno da imaju izvanrednu fizičku kondiciju. (*Majors* need to have excellent physical fitness.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "major" can be used as a noun, adjective, or possessive noun, and it has different forms for different cases (nominative, genitive, dative, accusative, vocative, and instrumental). In these sentences, I tried to showcase some of the most common ways the word can be used.